abstract = {Cyber Physical Systems (CPS) are almost everywhere; they can be accessed and controlled remotely. These features make them more vulnerable to cyber attacks. Since these systems provide critical services, having them under attack would have dangerous consequences. Unfortunately, cyber attacks may be detected, but after the damage is done. Therefore, developing a cyber system that can survive an attack is a challenge. In this paper, we are surveying the literature on security aspects of CPSs. First, we present some of existing methods for detecting cyber attacks. Second, we focus on three main cyber attacks, which are: Denial of service (DoS), deception, and replay attacks. In our discussion, we have surveyed some exiting models of these attacks, approaches of filtering CPS subject to these attacks, and approaches of control CPS subject to these attacks.}
